  "content": "\"font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;\">\n      NaN/infinity propagation in scores with no guards &bull; u32 overflow in access counts &bull; Missing boundary tests &bull; Stale build cache when env var changes\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <!-- Dynamic -->\n  <div class=\"card\" style=\"border-left: 4px solid var(--accent-purple); padding: 24px; margin-bottom: 0;\">\n    <div style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-purple); margin-bottom: 10px;\">&#128260; Dynamic Reviewers <span style=\"font-weight: 500; font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-muted);\">(created on the fly)</span></div>\n    <div style=\"font-size: 18px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.7;\">\n      Claude spawned a <span style=\"color: var(--accent-purple);\">Rust Idiom</span> reviewer that replaced 3 pin fields with Option&lt;PinInfo&gt; &bull;\n      A <span style=\"color: var(--accent-cyan);\">Security</span> reviewer it created caught session logs leaking prompt secrets &bull;\n      A <span style=\"color: var(--accent-cyan);\">Performance</span> reviewer turned O(S&times;E) &rarr; O(E) in a GC cycle\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"insight-box\" style=\"margin-top: 16px;\">\n    <p style=\"font-size: 18px;\">The SWE finds bugs. The QA finds missing tests. The PM finds incomplete work. The dynamic reviewers find what none of the above would think to look for.</p>\n  </div>\n\n  <div class=\"flex-grow\"></div>\n  <div class=\"author-tag\">Lim Chun Zhe</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-number\">05 / 09</div>\n</div>\n\n<!-- SLIDE 6: REVIEW OUTPUT EXAMPLE -->\n<div class=\"slide\">\n  <div class=\"slide-label\">What the Output Looks Like</div>\n  <div class=\"slide-title\" style=\"font-size: 52px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">\n    Real Review Output:<br>\n    <span class=\"highlight-purple\">HNSW Index Rebuild</span>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"slide-subtitle\" style=\"font-size: 20px; margin-bottom: 24px;\">\n    Actual findings from a single 5-persona review, triaged by severity.\n  </div>",
